# Unified Dependency Management (UDM) - UI Refactor Specification

## 1. Executive Summary
This document outlines the transition of the UDM plugin from a legacy tab-based category model (All / Installed / Updates / Browse) to a modern **JetBrains Rider-inspired** unified view. 

### 1.1 The Objective
To provide a seamless, IntelliJ-native experience where installed, transitive, and available packages are managed in a single, semantically grouped list.

### 1.2 Key UI Transformations
| Feature | Current UX (Legacy) | Future UX (Rider-Style) |
| :--- | :--- | :--- |
| **Organization** | Multiple tabs (Installed/Browse) | Single unified list with semantic grouping |
| **Transitivity** | Hidden dependencies | Explicit "Implicit" group with locked indicators |
| **Details Pane** | Verbose and cluttered | Compact, expandable sections with clear actions |
| **Status Cues** | Text-heavy status | Badges, icons, and color-coded versions |
| **Actions** | Limited toolbar actions | Rich context menus and "Upgrade All" workflows |

---

## 2. UI Architecture
The tool window uses a **Master-Detail** layout with a toolbar, optimized for high-density package management.

### 2.1 Component Hierarchy

```mermaid
graph TD
    A[UDM ToolWindow] --> B[JBTabbedPane]
    B --> C[Packages Tab]
    B --> D[Repositories Tab]
    B --> E[Log Tab]
    
    C --> F[ActionToolbar]
    C --> G[JSplitPane / Splitter]
    
    G --> H[Unified List Pane]
    G --> I[Details Pane]
    
    H --> H1[Installed Packages Section]
    H --> H2[Implicit Packages Section]
    H --> H3[Available Packages Section]
    
    I --> I1["Sticky Header (Icon/Name/Status)"]
    I --> I2["Version & Source Selectors"]
    I --> I3["Expandable: Description"]
    I --> I4["Expandable: Dependencies Tree"]
    I --> I5["Expandable: Module Usage"]
```

## 4. Interaction Specification

### 4.1 Global Principles
*   **Instant Feedback**: Action results (hover/click/upgrade) must trigger UI updates within 150ms.
*   **Zero-Mode Change**: No separate tabs for filtering; state is visual, not navigational.
*   **Micro-Transitions**: Fast animations (80-140ms) for expanding/collapsing sections.

### 4.2 List Interactions
*   **Hover**: Background highlight (`rgba(255,255,255,0.05)`).
*   **Selection**: Indigo border-left (`3px solid #7AA2F7`) and background.
*   **Transitive Locking**: Cursor shows `not-allowed`. Tooltip: *"Transitive dependency ‚Äî controlled by parent packages."*
*   **Search**: Debounced (150ms). Filters local sections immediately; triggers background fetch for "Available".

### 4.3 Status Indicators
*   **Outdated**: Version text turns orange; tooltip shows latest version.
*   **Vulnerable**: Red shield icon with security advisory link.
*   **Implicit**: Version in parentheses `(1.0.0)` to signal it's managed by another dependency.

---

## 5. Technical Implementation (Swing & IntelliJ SDK)

### 5.1 Tool Window & Tabbing
The plugin uses `ToolWindowFactory` to create the root container.
```kotlin
class UdpToolWindowFactory : ToolWindowFactory {
    override fun createToolWindowContent(project: Project, toolWindow: ToolWindow) {
        val root = JBTabbedPane().apply {
            addTab("Packages", PackagesTab(project).component)
            addTab("Repositories", RepositoriesTab(project).component)
            addTab("Log", LogTab(project).component)
        }
        val content = ContentFactory.getInstance().createContent(root, "", false)
        toolWindow.contentManager.addContent(content)
    }
}
```

### 5.2 Unified List (Grouping)
Two approaches are valid for the grouped list:
1.  **Option A (Tree)**: Use `Tree` with hidden root and visible section nodes (Installed, Implicit, Available).
2.  **Option B (JBList)**: A single list with custom `ListCellRenderer` that draws non-selectable header rows.

### 5.3 Action System Integration
Toolbar controls should be implemented as `AnAction` objects to support keyboard shortcuts and consistent styling.
*   **Search**: `SearchTextField`
*   **Toggles**: `JBCheckBox` or `OnOffButton`
*   **Popups**: `JBPopupFactory` for context menus.

## 6. Workflow Diagrams

### 6.1 Package Search & Resolve
```mermaid
flowchart TD
    A[User Types Search] --> B[Debounce 150ms]
    B --> C[Filter Local List]
    B --> D[Background Repo Query]
    D --> E[Update Available Section]
    C --> F[Refresh UI]
    E --> F
```

### 6.2 Bulk Upgrade Workflow
```mermaid
flowchart TD
    A[Click Upgrade All] --> B[Open Upgrade Dialog]
    B --> C[Select Versions & Options]
    C --> D[Apply version changes to build files]
    D --> E[Trigger IDE Sync/Resolve]
    E --> F[Refresh Unified List]
    F --> G[Show Completion Notification]
```
